Experiencing disappointments in a romantic relationship is a risk everybody faces. It may strike suddenly or build up slowly, but it’s common among couples. When you fail to address the frustrations of your past relationship in a healthy manner, you deprive yourself of learning better ways to love and make yourself happy. And this can affect your future relationships. Here are a few Dos and Don’ts to help you manage life after a heartbreak. Dos: Don’ts: There’s no quick recipe to help you get over a failed relationship. Your value doesn’t decrease as a result of someone else’s inability to see it.